learn from the markdown to html tag mapping, we need to support those {
  - # => h1
  - ## => h2
  - ### => h3
  - **bold text** => strong:bold text
  - *italicized text* => italic:italicized text
  - > blockquote => blockquote
  - 1. First item
    2. Second Item
    3. Third Item
    =>
    ol {
      li:First Item
      li:Second Item
      li:Third Item
    }
  - - First item
    - Second item
    - Third item
    =>
    ul {
      li:First Item
      li:Second Item
      li:Third Item
    }
  - `code` => code { code }
    or code {
      code
    }
    or code: code
  - --- => hr
  - [google](https://www.google.com) => link:google:https://www.google.com
  - ![alt text](image.jpg) => img:text:img.jpg
}

for (i = 1; i<=3; i++) {
  learn from the source prompt ./tests/test_markdown_{i}.prompt
  learn from the target generated markdown that are generated from the source prompt, ./tests/test_markdown_{i}.md
}
learn from {
  - https://github.com/scopewu/qrcode.vue/blob/f6929f8047e67d1399d6e65030bd73c2184c0c16/AGENTS.md?plain=1
  - https://github.com/derrickburns/generalized-kmeans-clustering/blob/master/AGENTS.md?plain=1
  - https://github.com/kmifka/hass_lmair/blob/480b1d24d06586ff36f42726749c46487f3fbfd8/Agents.md?plain=1
  - https://github.com/deanthecoder/G33kBoy/blob/9e0a83bb5376db3b5490f73e4aac3f8ded33021d/agents.md?plain=1
}

